		<div class="comment_text"><p>I think some techniques are labeled as advanced for a reason.</p><p>Will "advanced" techniques make your coding better? Maybe so, but I don't think they are essential to getting started.</p><p>My first ColdFusion application was a collection of worst practices. Still, in less than a month I had an application that was well-received in my organization.</p><p>From there, I learned better techniques (much of that from the pain of trying to maintain that first application). If I had tried to learn everything before I got started, it would have taken a lot longer and I wouldn't have understand where and why to do the more advanced stuff anyway.</p><p>As Dave says, you need a good grasp of the basics before you learn the advanced stuff. You should learn it, but start with the basics first.</p></div>
